Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and half of the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1/2%pack}, toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the wedges nicely spread out.

Soak the @bamboo skewers{4} in a #bowl{} of cold water (to prevent them from burning). Drain and chop the @halloumi{250%g} into 2cm chunks. Place them into another bowl of cold water and leave to soak. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into 2cm wide strips, then chop into roughly 2cm pieces. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Chop the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm pieces. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry. Then pop them into a bowl with the pepper, lemon zest, a drizzle of oil, a grind of pepper and the remaining @Central American Style Spice Mix{1/2%pack}. Mix well to combine and carefully thread them onto the skewers (2 skewers per person). Alternate between halloumi and pepper. Pop the skewers onto a #baking tray{}.

Once the wedges are halfway through cooking, bake the skewers on the middle shelf of your oven until the halloumi is golden and the pepper is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. In the meantime, combine the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @sweet chilli sauce{3%tbsp} in a small bowl, mix well to combine.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the baby gem and tomato. Squeeze over half of the lemon juice and drizzle over the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @sugar{pinch} (if you have any). Toss to coat.

Once the halloumi skewers are out of the oven, drizzle over the @honey{15%ml} and share between your plates. Pop the wedges and salad alongside, drizzle the sweet chilli mayo all over the skewers. Enjoy!